I'm giving 1 star because customer service is everything. I found the guy behind the counter to be extremely unfriendly. When I asked to modify something in my sandwich he sighed and rolled his eyes and said "you should have told me earlier". I've come here a few times because the food itself is not bad but I do have to comment on the Sabich - they do NOT HAVE Amba - which is essential condiment in a Sabich. I prefer to frequent an establishment where I get a friendly smile when I walk in, instead of impatience or apathy. That's all.

I tried this place for the first time. Ordered 2 egg-avocado sandwiches. They *both* had eggshells in them that I had to pick out. The sandwiches are not made with any care or seasoning. The ingredients are stuffed in such a way that they’re separate inside, so you’re getting only onions or only egg in one bite. You basically have to deconstruct the sandwich and redistribute everything evenly. This place also skimps on the main ingredients. Our sandwiches, which we ordered mainly for the avocado aspect, had one measly piece of avocado with 2 sliced eggs and then just stuffed full of onions. Overall would not come here again.

I live around the corner from Wrap and Roll. It is my go-to place for nights when I don't want to cook, and especially the week before Pesach. The place is very clean. The food is fresh and tasty, not greasy.  I especially recommend their spicy lentil soup. The owners are very nice people.
